{"sequence":17,"timestamp":"2026-04-10T06:15:49.334554953Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-14fa4a43","body":"Fix stale writer-lock recovery before `run resume`/`run stop` rely on the new PID-based stale-run flow. `handle_resume` still acquires the CLI writer lease before any stale-Running reconciliation (`src/cli/run.rs:1769-1778`), and `CliWriterLeaseGuard::acquire` hard-fails on an existing lock (`src/contexts/automation_runtime/cli_writer_lease.rs:136-166`). The new stale-stop/interruption paths only rewrite `run.json`/`run.pid` (`src/cli/run.rs:1885-1941`, `src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:729-757`) and never release or reclaim the old writer lock. After a SIGKILL/OOM/crash, the run is reported as stale, but `run resume` can still fail with `ProjectWriterLockHeld` until daemon TTL/reconcile clears the stale lease. Add lease cleanup/reclamation to stale-run recovery, or move the stale detection ahead of lock acquisition so the recovery path can clear the stranded lock before trying to resume.","dedup_key":"572acfb53a4435a2518eade41a38d8441a3f0aa3ed2c0d688622c318586b4fb6","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260410054251","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":18,"timestamp":"2026-04-10T06:15:49.344245364Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-66744da8","body":"Remove the startup race where a live run can be misclassified as stale before `run.pid` exists. The engine writes `run.json` as `Running` before creating the pid file on both start and resume (`src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:1080-1115`, `src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:1806-1849`), but `run status` and `run stop` immediately treat a missing pid file as proof that the orchestrator is dead (`src/cli/run.rs:1885-1899`, `src/cli/run.rs:5319-5338`). In that window, `run status` reports a healthy run as stale, and `run stop` can mark the snapshot failed without ever signaling the still-running orchestrator. Either write the pid file before exposing `Running`, or make `status`/`stop` tolerate the pre-pid startup window and/or coordinate with the writer lease.","dedup_key":"7700f09150e11abd621d917bc50fa278c7bfca738e3c2c98b737986bab92abb3","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260410054251","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
